Set the scene
For the sake of example, let‚Äôs suppose the task I want to do is count how many ones are in a particular column.
I‚Äôve written a nice function, using tunneling ({{}}) to run on unquoted variable names.


count_ones &lt;- function(data, var) {

  data |&gt;
    summarize(
      n_ones = sum({{var}} == 1)
    ) |&gt;
    pull(n_ones)

}

count_ones(mtcars, vs)
#&gt; [1] 14

Fabulous. We could clean this output up a bit, but we won‚Äôt, because lazy.
So, the question is, what if I want to do this to multiple columns at once?
